urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.593#And Zeus, the master of cloud and storm:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.594#"You witch! Your intuitions are always right.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.595#But what does it get you? Nothing, except that
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.596#I like you less than ever. And so you're worse off.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.597#If it's as you think it is, it's my business, not yours.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.598#So sit down and shut up and do as I say.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.599#You see these hands? All the gods on Olympus
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.600#Won't be able to help you if I ever lay them on you."
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.601#Hera lost her nerve when she heard this.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.602#She sat down in silence, fear cramping her heart,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.603#And gloom settled over the gods in Zeus' hall.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.604#Hephaestus, the master artisan, broke the silence,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.605#Out of concern for his ivory-armed mother:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.606#"This is terrible; it's going to ruin us all.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.607#If you two quarrel like this over mortals
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.608#It's bound to affect us gods. There'll be no more
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.609#Pleasure in our feasts if we let things turn ugly.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.610#Mother, please, I don't have to tell you,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.611#You have to be pleasant to our father Zeus
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.612#So he won't be angry and ruin our feast.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.613#If the Lord of Lightning wants to blast us from our seats,
