urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.615#So apologize to him with silken-soft words,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.616#And the Olympian in turn will be gracious to us."
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.617#He whisked up a two-handled cup, offered it
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.618#To his dear mother, and said to her:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.619#"I know it's hard, mother, but you have to endure it.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.620#I don't want to see you getting beat up, and me
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.621#Unable to help you. The Olympian can be rough.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:1.622#Once before when I tried to rescue you
