urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.20#The Dream listened and went. Shadows flew
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.21#Around the Greek ships. It found Agamemnon
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.22#Wrapped in deep, starlit slumber.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.23#The Dream stood above his head. It looked
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.24#Like Nestor, the old man that Agamemnon
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.25#Respected the most, looked just like Nestor,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.26#And this dream that was a god addressed the king:
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.27#"Asleep, son of Atreus, horsebreaker,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.28#Wise man? You can't sleep all night.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:2.29#All those decisions to make, so many people
