urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:14.221#She spoke, and ox-eyed Hera,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:14.222#Smiling, tucked the sash in her bosom.
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:14.223#Then Zeus' daughter Aphrodite went home,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:14.224#But Hera streaked down from Olympus' peak,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:14.225#Used Pieria and Emathia as stepping stones,
urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.sl:14.226#And sped over the snowcapped mountains
